<item>
            <title>[FELIX-4023] SCR-Plugin not working reliably in m2e 1.3.1</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-4023</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The default lifecycle-mapping assumed by m2e changed in version 1.3. see &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;. The default for runOnIncremental is now false and as the scr-plugin does not specify otherwise in it&apos;s embedded lifecycle-mapping descriptor, it no longer is invoked when the user edits source files inside eclipse. Only when a complete rebuild of the project is triggered the plugin is executed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The embedded lifecycle-mapping should be changed to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;action&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;execute&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;runOnIncremental&amp;gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&amp;lt;/runOnIncremental&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;/execute&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/action&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=395433&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=395433&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Eclipse 4.2.2 w/ m2e 1.3.1</environment>
